{
  "$schema": "https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema",
  "$id": "https://aureline.dev/schemas/companion/add-incident-workspace-headers-evidence-timelines-resource-slices-and-runbook-packets.schema.json",
  "title": "Aureline incident workspace headers, evidence timelines, resource slices, and runbook packets",
  "description": "Export-safe packet for the incident workspace content: the header card that identifies an incident, the ordered evidence timeline (including first-class missing spans), the read-only resource slices attributed to the incident, and the runbook packets that guide mitigation. It projects four sections — header, evidence_timeline, resource_slice, and runbook_packet — each inheriting qualification from the frozen M5 companion-matrix incident_workspace lane, and gives every item an exact desktop handoff. Read-mostly and attributable: every section is read-only, a runbook never executes an automated step without explicit host approval, and a header or evidence span that loses attribution narrows to unattributed rather than claiming a provenance it cannot prove; a missing evidence span is recorded as a first-class fact. Stale-state honesty: every item carries a freshness state, stale or unknown freshness is always labeled, and a degraded item is never shown as live. Degraded state (relay unavailable, stale proof, inactive host, narrowed trust, lost incident attribution, incomplete evidence, narrowed upstream lane, unresolved handoff, downgraded freshness) is labeled rather than hidden. Credential bodies, raw provider payloads, and raw incident, evidence, resource, or runbook bodies never cross this boundary.",
